        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Mechanism Synthesis</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: the application of geometry to find a mechanism that provides a design requirement. The requirements include: Position Synthesis, Function Generation, Coupler Point Synthesis. There are three stages Mechanism Synthesis: </text></para>
          <list id="11" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Type Synthesis</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> (gives the type of mechanism: linkages, gears, cams, belts...)</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Number Synthesis</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> (gives the number of Parts, how many degrees-of-freedom)</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Dimensional Synthesis</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> (gives the exact lengths of Parts, the exact Cam-Profile)</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
